HTTP Requests:
Client requests on the internet are made in the form of HTTP.

Client:
Anyone who makes a request.

Server:
A program that receives a request from the client, processes it, and returns a response.

HTTP Methods:
The entire web functions with the help of HTTP requests and responses, making HTTP methods the backbone of these communications.

Types of HTTP Methods:
GET: Used to retrieve data from the server.
POST: Used to send data to the server, often to create or update a resource.
PUT: Used to update an existing resource or create a new one if it doesnâ€™t exist.
DELETE: Used to delete a specific resource on the server.
